DFA NFA simulator
###########################################################################################################################################################################################################
This is a lex program which implements a generic table driven lexical analyzer to verify a given input string against a DFA or NFA represented in form of a transition table

******************************************************************* NOTE: Attached input.txt and specification.txt, So modify it accordingly ********************************************************************

To run the program:
1)Go to the project directory
2)To build the lex program run "make" command without quotes
3)To run the executable run the command as given in the question "./mylex _ _ _ _" without quotes and replacing those _ with corresponding input, where first space is to tell whether it is a NFA or DFA and second _ specifies number of states, third _ specifies number of final states and fourth _ specifies the number of input symbols
4)To remove executable and output file run "make remove" command without quotes

###########################################################################################################################################################################################################
